[[File:Ruth Bisibori Nyangau.jpg|thumb|200px|Ruth Bosibori]]
'''Ruth Bosibori Nyangau''' (also written '''Ruth Bisibori;''' born 2 January 1988 in [[Bosiango]]) is a [[Kenya]]n middle distance runner who specializes in the [[3000 metres steeplechase]].

In July 2007 she became the first [[Athletics at the 2007 All-Africa Games|All-Africa Games]] champion in the event, as it was staged for the first time. In August the same year she finished fourth at the [[2007 World Championships in Athletics - Women's 3000 metres steeplechase|World Championships]] in a [[World junior records in athletics|world junior record]] time of 9:25.25 minutes. The old record was 9:30.70 and belonged to [[Melissa Rollison]].<ref>[http://www.iaaf.org/statistics/toplists/inout=O/ageGroup=J/season=0/gender=W/discipline=3KSC/legal=A/index.html IAAF top lists - 3000 Metres Steeplechase Junior]</ref>. At the [[2008 African Championships in Athletics]] she finished third <ref>[http://www.addis2008.org/Results/Data/at/asf/023/004/cgcgr3atasf023l004001.html Addis 2008 results]</ref>.

Bosibori was born in Bosiango village near [[Kisii, Kenya|Kisii]] <ref>Daily Nation, November 2, 2007: [http://www.nationmedia.com/dailynation/nmgcontententry.asp?category_id=5&newsid=109690 Bosibori's world record ratified] </ref>. 
She started running in 2003 while at Kebirichi Secondary School. She was recruited by [[Kenya Police]] after winning provincial championships in 2007 <ref>The Standard, August 19, 2007: ''[http://www.eastandard.net/archives/sunday/hm_news/news.php?articleid=1143973131 Humble Bosibori to keep tradition]''</ref>. She is used to [[barefoot running|competing barefoot]] <ref>Japan Times, August 29, 2007: ''[http://search.japantimes.co.jp/rss/sp20070829t5.html Worlds notebook; Day 4]''</ref>.

She won the Most Promising Sportswoman of the Year category at the 2007 [[Kenyan Sports Personality of the Year]] awards <ref>[http://www.soyaawards.com/winners.html SOYA Awards - 2007 winners]</ref>. She is coached by [[Dan Muchoki]] <ref>IAAF: August 4, 2007: [http://www.iaaf.org/news/athletes/newsid=40761.html Focus on Africa - Ruth BOSIBORI]</ref>.

